      <p>No timeline on these yet. Astro is the focus until v1.0 is solid.</p>

      <hr />

      <h2 id="troubleshooting">Troubleshooting</h2>

      <h3>Components not showing up</h3>
      <ol>
        <li>
          Check that <code>stargazer.config.ts</code> exists in project root
        </li>
        <li>
          Verify <code>path</code> values start with <code>./</code> and are relative
          to project root
        </li>
        <li>
          Run <code>npm run dev</code> and check console for <code
            >[astro-stargazer] Found X component(s)</code
          >
        </li>
        <li>
          In <code>mode: 'auto'</code>, make sure the component is inside <code
            >src/</code
          > and not in an excluded path
        </li>
      </ol>

      <h3>Styles missing in preview</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>
          Set <code>defaultLayout</code> to a layout that imports your global CSS
        </li>
        <li>
          Components without a layout show <code>⚠ no layout</code> in the index
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Layout not wrapping correctly</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>
          Ensure your layout uses <code>&lt;slot /&gt;</code> to render children
        </li>
        <li>
          Verify the layout key in <code>components</code> matches a key in <code
            >layouts</code
          >
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Stargazer not in production</h3>
      <p>
        By design — dev-only. Set <code>buildable: true</code> to include it in production
        builds.
      </p>
      <blockquote>
        <p>
          <strong>Important:</strong> When using <code>buildable: true</code>,
          your Astro project <strong
            >must have a server adapter configured</strong
          > (<a
            href="https://www.cloudflare.com"
            target="_blank"
            class="fw-link">Cloudflare</a
          >, <a href="https://vercel.com" target="_blank" class="fw-link"
            >Vercel</a
          >, <a href="https://www.netlify.com" target="_blank" class="fw-link"
            >Netlify</a
          >, <a href="https://nodejs.org" target="_blank" class="fw-link"
            >Node</a
          >, etc.). Stargazer's routes are SSR-only.
        </p>
      </blockquote>

      <h3>Dark mode toggle not working</h3>
      <p>CSS must respond to the method you configured:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <code>attribute</code>: <code>[color-scheme="dark"]</code> on <code
            >&lt;html&gt;</code
          >
        </li>
        <li><code>class</code>: <code>html.dark</code></li>
        <li>
          <code>data-theme</code>: <code>[data-theme="dark"]</code> on <code
            >&lt;html&gt;</code
          >
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Search bar not showing up</h3>
      <p>
        The search input only appears when there are <strong
          >more than 4 components</strong
        > registered.
      </p>

      <h3>Copy Props button doesn't work</h3>
      <p>
        The Clipboard API requires either <strong>HTTPS or localhost</strong>.
        It won't work over plain HTTP on a network address.
      </p>

      <h3>Zoom buttons are not showing</h3>
      <p>
        Zoom only appears when the selected viewport is <strong>≤ 1024px</strong
        >. At larger viewports there is no zoom.
      </p>

      <h3>Can I change the <code>/stargazer</code> URL?</h3>
      <p>Yes. Set the <code>base</code> option in your config:</p>
      <pre><code>const config: StargazerConfig = {'{'} 
  base: '/preview',
{'}'};</code></pre>

      <h3>My site switched to hybrid output — will this break my build?</h3>
      <p>
        No. Stargazer temporarily switches <code>output</code> to <code
          >hybrid</code
        >
        <strong>in memory during <code>astro dev</code></strong> so its SSR routes
        work. This change is never written to your config file and does not affect
        <code>astro build</code>.
      </p>
      <table>
        <thead><tr><th>Command</th><th>Effect</th></tr></thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr
            ><td><code>astro dev</code></td><td
              >Stargazer active, output set to <code>hybrid</code> in memory only</td
            ></tr
          >
          <tr
            ><td><code>astro build</code></td><td
              >Stargazer skipped entirely — your output stays <code>static</code
              ></td
            ></tr
          >
          <tr
            ><td><code>astro build</code> + <code>buildable: true</code></td><td
              >Stargazer included, output set to <code>hybrid</code>, <strong
                >requires a server adapter</strong
              ></td
            ></tr
          >
        </tbody>
      </table>

      <h3>What adapter should I use with <code>buildable: true</code>?</h3>
      <p>
        Any official Astro adapter works: <code>@astrojs/cloudflare</code>, <code
          >@astrojs/vercel</code
        >, <code>@astrojs/netlify</code>, <code>@astrojs/node</code>. Configure
        it as you normally would — Stargazer does not add any adapter-specific
        code.
      </p>
      <p>
        If your project currently uses <code>output: 'static'</code> with no adapter,
        the simplest option for staging is <code>@astrojs/node</code> in standalone
        mode. Or just leave <code>buildable</code> at its default <code
          >false</code
        > and use Stargazer in dev only.
      </p>

      <h3>Component shows an error page</h3>
      <p>
        The error boundary caught a failure. Read the error message shown in the
        iframe, fix the component, click Reload.
      </p>
      <p>
        If the error says <strong
          ><code>Cannot read properties of undefined</code></strong
        >, the component is trying to use a prop that wasn't passed. This is
        common in <code>auto</code> mode. Fix by adding the required prop to <code
          >defaults</code
        >:
      </p>
      <pre><code>const config: StargazerConfig = {'{'} 
  mode: 'auto',
  defaults: {'{'} 
    lang: 'en',   // fix: 'Cannot read properties of undefined (reading "contact")'
  {'}'},
{'}'};</code></pre>

      <h3>Preview is blank but shows no error</h3>
      <p>
        The component probably renders no visible HTML — empty output,
        whitespace only, or a <code>display: none</code> element. Check the component
        itself and open the browser devtools inside the iframe to inspect.
      </p>

      <hr />

      <p
        style="text-align: center; color: var(--text-muted); margin-top: 48px; font-size: 13px;"
      >
        <a
          href="https://github.com/webxtekagency/astro-stargazer/blob/main/LICENSE"
          target="_blank"
          class="fw-link">MIT</a
        > © <a href="https://webxtek.com" target="_blank" class="fw-link"
          >Webxtek</a
        > · Built with <a
          href="https://astro.build"
          target="_blank"
          class="fw-link">Astro</a
        >
      </p>
    </main>

    <button
      class="scroll-up-btn"
      id="scroll-up-btn"
      aria-label="Scroll to top"
      title="Scroll to top"
    >
      <svg
        viewBox="0 0 24 24"
        width="18"
        height="18"
        fill="none"
        stroke="currentColor"
        stroke-width="2"
        stroke-linecap="round"
        stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M12 19V5M5 12l7-7 7 7"></path></svg
      >
    </button>

    <script>
      const links = document.querySelectorAll(".sidebar-link");
      const sections: { el: HTMLElement; link: Element }[] = [];
      links.forEach((link) => {
        const href = link.getAttribute("href");
        if (href && href.startsWith("#")) {
          const el = document.getElementById(href.slice(1));
          if (el) sections.push({ el, link });
        }
      });

      function updateSpy() {
        const scrollY = window.scrollY + 80;
        let current = sections[0];
        for (const s of sections) {
          if (s.el.offsetTop <= scrollY) current = s;
        }
        if (current && !current.link.classList.contains("active")) {
          links.forEach((l) => l.classList.remove("active"));
          current.link.classList.add("active");
          const sb = document.getElementById("docs-sidebar");
          if (sb) {
            const le = current.link as HTMLElement;
            sb.scrollTo({
              top: le.offsetTop - sb.clientHeight / 2,
              behavior: "smooth",
            });
          }
        }
      }
      window.addEventListener("scroll", updateSpy, { passive: true });
      updateSpy();

      const toggle = document.getElementById("sidebar-toggle");
      const sidebar = document.getElementById("docs-sidebar");
      if (toggle && sidebar) {
        toggle.addEventListener("click", () =>
          sidebar.classList.toggle("open"),
        );
        sidebar.addEventListener("click", (e: Event) => {
          const target = e.target as HTMLElement;
          if (target.classList.contains("sidebar-link")) {
            sidebar.classList.remove("open");
          }
        });
      }

      const searchInput = document.getElementById(
        "docs-search",
      ) as HTMLInputElement | null;
      const ddrop = document.getElementById("docs-search-dropdown");
      if (searchInput && ddrop) {
        type SearchItem = {
          text: string;
          id: string;
          parent: string;
          kind: "heading" | "body";
        };
        const items: SearchItem[] = [];
        const mc = document.querySelector(".docs-content");
        if (mc) {
          let currentH2 = "";
          let currentAnchorId = "";

          mc.querySelectorAll("h2, h3, p, li").forEach((el) => {
            const tag = el.tagName;

            if (tag === "H2") {
              const id = el.getAttribute("id");
              const text = el.textContent?.trim() || "";
              if (!id || !text) return;
              currentH2 = text;
              currentAnchorId = id;
              items.push({ text, id, parent: "", kind: "heading" });
            } else if (tag === "H3") {
              const text = el.textContent?.trim() || "";
              if (!text) return;
              let id = el.getAttribute("id");
              if (!id) {
                id =
                  "h3-" +
                  text
                    .toLowerCase()
                    .replace(/[^a-z0-9]+/g, "-")
                    .slice(0, 40);
                el.setAttribute("id", id);
              }
              currentAnchorId = id;
              items.push({ text, id, parent: currentH2, kind: "heading" });
            } else {
              if (!currentAnchorId) return;
              const text = (el.textContent?.trim() || "").replace(/\s+/g, " ");
              if (text.length < 10) return;
              items.push({
                text,
                id: currentAnchorId,
                parent: currentH2,
                kind: "body",
              });
            }
          });
        }

        let hi = -1;
        function render(q: string) {
          const low = q.toLowerCase();
          if (!low) {
            ddrop!.classList.remove("open");
            ddrop!.innerHTML = "";
            return;
          }

          const headingMatches = items.filter(
            (i) =>
              i.kind === "heading" &&
              (i.text.toLowerCase().includes(low) ||
                i.parent.toLowerCase().includes(low)),
          );

          const headingIds = new Set(headingMatches.map((i) => i.id));
          const bodyMatches: SearchItem[] = [];
          const seenBodyIds = new Set<string>();
          for (const i of items) {
            if (i.kind !== "body") continue;
            if (!i.text.toLowerCase().includes(low)) continue;
            if (headingIds.has(i.id)) continue;
            if (seenBodyIds.has(i.id)) continue;
            seenBodyIds.add(i.id);
            bodyMatches.push(i);
          }

          const m = [...headingMatches, ...bodyMatches];
          hi = -1;
          if (!m.length) {
            ddrop!.classList.remove("open");
            ddrop!.innerHTML = "";
            return;
          }

          ddrop!.innerHTML = m
            .map((x, i) => {
              const snippet =
                x.kind === "body"
                  ? `<div class="docs-search-item-section">${x.parent || "Content"} — ${x.text.slice(0, 60)}…</div>`
                  : x.parent
                    ? `<div class="docs-search-item-section">${x.parent}</div>`
                    : "";
              return `<a class="docs-search-item" href="#${x.id}" data-i="${i}">${x.text}${snippet}</a>`;
            })
            .join("");
          ddrop!.classList.add("open");
        }
        searchInput!.addEventListener("input", () =>
          render(searchInput!.value),
        );
        searchInput!.addEventListener("keydown", (e: KeyboardEvent) => {
          const els = ddrop!.querySelectorAll(".docs-search-item");
          if (e.key === "ArrowDown") {
            e.preventDefault();
            hi = Math.min(hi + 1, els.length - 1);
          } else if (e.key === "ArrowUp") {
            e.preventDefault();
            hi = Math.max(hi - 1, 0);
          } else if (e.key === "Enter" && hi >= 0 && els[hi]) {
            e.preventDefault();
            (els[hi] as HTMLAnchorElement).click();
            ddrop!.classList.remove("open");
            searchInput!.blur();
            return;
          } else if (e.key === "Escape") {
            searchInput!.value = "";
            ddrop!.classList.remove("open");
            searchInput!.blur();
            return;
          } else return;
          els.forEach((el, i) => el.classList.toggle("highlight", i === hi));
        });
        ddrop!.addEventListener("click", () => {
          ddrop!.classList.remove("open");
          searchInput!.value = "";
        });
        document.addEventListener("click", (e: Event) => {
          if (!(e.target as HTMLElement).closest(".docs-search-wrap"))
            ddrop!.classList.remove("open");
        });
        document.addEventListener("keydown", (e: KeyboardEvent) => {
          if (
            e.key === "/" &&
            document.activeElement !== searchInput &&
            !(document.activeElement as HTMLElement)?.matches?.(
              "input,textarea",
            )
          ) {
            e.preventDefault();
            searchInput!.focus();
          }
        });
      }
      const scrollBtn = document.getElementById("scroll-up-btn");
      if (scrollBtn) {
        const getScrollY = () =>
          window.scrollY ||
          document.body.scrollTop ||
          document.documentElement.scrollTop;
        const onScroll = () => {
          if (getScrollY() > 300) scrollBtn.classList.add("visible");
          else scrollBtn.classList.remove("visible");
        };
        window.addEventListener("scroll", onScroll, { passive: true });
        document.addEventListener("scroll", onScroll, { passive: true });
        document.body.addEventListener("scroll", onScroll, { passive: true });
        scrollBtn.addEventListener("click", () => {
          window.scrollTo({ top: 0, behavior: "smooth" });
          document.body.scrollTo({ top: 0, behavior: "smooth" });
          document.documentElement.scrollTop = 0;
        });
      }

      function setTheme(theme: "light" | "dark") {
        document.documentElement.setAttribute("data-theme", theme);
        localStorage.setItem("stargazer-theme", theme);
        document.querySelectorAll(".sg-theme-btn").forEach((b) => {
          if (b.getAttribute("data-theme") === theme) b.classList.add("active");
          else b.classList.remove("active");
        });
      }
      (window as any).setTheme = setTheme;

      const savedTheme = localStorage.getItem("stargazer-theme") as
        | "light"
        | "dark"
        | null;
      const prefersLight =
        window.matchMedia &&
        window.matchMedia("(prefers-color-scheme: light)").matches;
      setTheme(savedTheme || (prefersLight ? "light" : "dark"));

      window.addEventListener("storage", (e) => {
        if (e.key === "stargazer-theme" && e.newValue) {
          setTheme(e.newValue as "light" | "dark");
        }
      });

      function esc(s: string) {
        return s
          .replace(/&/g, "&amp;")
          .replace(/</g, "&lt;")
          .replace(/>/g, "&gt;");
      }
      function highlightWords(plain: string) {
        return esc(plain)
          .replace(
            /\b(export|default|import|from|const|let|var|function|return|if|else|for|while|class|extends|new|typeof|instanceof|async|await|try|catch|throw|type|interface|satisfies|in|of|as|true|false|null|undefined)\b/g,
            (m) => {
              if (/^(true|false|null|undefined)$/.test(m))
                return `<span class="tok-boolean">${m}</span>`;
              return `<span class="tok-keyword">${m}</span>`;
            },
          )
          .replace(
            /\b([A-Z][A-Za-z0-9_]+)\b/g,
            '<span class="tok-type">$1</span>',
          )
          .replace(
            /\b(\d+(?:\.\d+)?)\b/g,
            '<span class="tok-number">$1</span>',
          );
      }
      function highlightCode(text: string) {
        const tok =
          /(\/\/[^\n]*)|(\/\*[\s\S]*?\*\/)|(`[^`]*`|'[^'\\]*(?:\\.[^'\\]*)*'|"[^"\\]*(?:\\.[^"\\]*)*")/g;
        let result = "";
        let last = 0;
        let m: RegExpExecArray | null;
        while ((m = tok.exec(text)) !== null) {
          result += highlightWords(text.slice(last, m.index));
          const raw = esc(m[0]);
          if (m[1] || m[2]) result += `<span class="tok-comment">${raw}</span>`;
          else result += `<span class="tok-string">${raw}</span>`;
          last = tok.lastIndex;
        }
        result += highlightWords(text.slice(last));
        return result;
      }

      document.querySelectorAll(".docs-content table").forEach((table) => {
        const wrap = document.createElement("div");
        wrap.className = "table-scroll";
        table.parentNode?.insertBefore(wrap, table);
        wrap.appendChild(table);
      });

      document.querySelectorAll(".docs-content pre").forEach((pre) => {
        const wrapper = document.createElement("div");
        wrapper.className = "docs-pre-wrapper";
        pre.parentNode?.insertBefore(wrapper, pre);
        wrapper.appendChild(pre);
        (pre as HTMLElement).style.overflow = "auto";
        (pre as HTMLElement).style.height = "100%";

        const header = document.createElement("div");
        header.className = "docs-pre-header";

        const code = pre.querySelector("code");
        const rawText = code?.textContent?.trim() || "";

        function detectLang(text: string) {
          const first = text.split("\n")[0].trim();
          if (
            /^(npm|npx|pnpm|yarn|git|cd |ls |mkdir|cp |mv |rm |cat |echo |node |tsx? |astro )/.test(
              first,
            )
          )
            return "shell";
          if (/^(#|\/\/\s*astro\.config|defineConfig|---\n)/.test(first))
            return "typescript";
          if (
            /^\s*(import|export|const|let|var|interface|type |function|class |async )/.test(
              text,
            )
          )
            return "typescript";
          if (/^([\w-]+:\s|---$)/.test(first)) return "yaml";
          return "typescript";
        }
        const detectedLang = detectLang(rawText);

        const lang = document.createElement("span");
        lang.className = "docs-pre-lang";
        lang.textContent = detectedLang;
        header.appendChild(lang);

        const btn = document.createElement("button");
        btn.className = "copy-btn";
        btn.innerHTML = `<svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><rect x="9" y="9" width="13" height="13" rx="2" ry="2"></rect><path d="M5 15H4a2 2 0 0 1-2-2V4a2 2 0 0 1 2-2h9a2 2 0 0 1 2 2v1"></path></svg> COPY`;
        header.appendChild(btn);

        wrapper.insertBefore(header, pre);

        if (code) {
          code.innerHTML = highlightCode(code.textContent || "");
        }

        btn.addEventListener("click", async (e) => {
          e.stopPropagation();
          const codeEl = pre.querySelector("code");
          if (!codeEl) return;
          try {
            await navigator.clipboard.writeText(codeEl.textContent || "");
            btn.classList.add("copied");
            btn.innerHTML = `<svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"></polyline></svg> COPIED`;
            setTimeout(() => {
              btn.classList.remove("copied");
